        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>I would say our abil­ity to con­tinue on this path of pro­gres­sive re­sump­tion of ac­tiv­i­ties rests largely on two fac­tors: One, we have to con­trol the in­fec­tion and keep num­bers down... Se­condly, it also de­pends on our abil­ity to com­ply with ex­ist­ing mea­sures, be­cause if we are not even able to keep to the ex­ist­ing mea­sures, then why even talk about fur­ther lib­er­al­i­sa­tions or eas­ing, which will cause more prob­lems down the road? So, we re­ally seek ev­ery­one’s co­op­er­a­tion.</p>
    <p>ED­U­CA­TION MIN­IS­TER LAWRENCE WONG, who co-chairs the multi-min­istry task force tack­ling Covid-19.</p>


